<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,153,468]" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">
Remarks: The 
<typeStatus box="[316,414,333,359]" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Perez, 1907" authorityName="Perez" authorityYear="1907" box="[452,737,333,359]" class="Insecta" family="Scoliidae" genus="Discolia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="senescens">
<emphasis box="[452,597,334,359]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">D. senescens</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Perez, J." box="[605,737,333,359]" pageId="3" pageNumber="179" pagination="485 - 505" refId="ref4379" refString="Perez, J. (1907) Mission J. Bonnier et Ch. Perez. (Golfe Persique, 1901). II - Hymenopteres. Bulletin Scientifique de la France et de la Belgique, 41, 485 - 505. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 21339" type="journal article" year="1907">Pérez, 1907</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is apparently lost (
<bibRefCitation author="Betrem, J. G." box="[951,1102,333,360]" pageId="3" pageNumber="179" pagination="1 - 78" refId="ref3133" refString="Betrem, J. G. (1935) Beitrag zur Kenntnis der palaarktischen Arten des Genus Scolia. Tijdschrift voor Entomologie, 78, 1 - 78." type="journal article" year="1935">Betrem 1935</bibRefCitation>
), so the status of that taxon is uncertain; 
<bibRefCitation author="Osten, T." box="[320,482,369,396]" pageId="3" pageNumber="179" pagination="1 - 62" refId="ref4213" refString="Osten, T. (2005 b) Checkliste der Dolchwespen der Welt (Insecta: Hymenoptera, Scoliidae). Bericht der Naturforschenden Gesellschaft Augsburg, 62, 1 - 62." type="journal article" year="2005">Osten (2005b)</bibRefCitation>
regarded it as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Saussure" authorityYear="1859" box="[834,949,370,396]" class="Insecta" family="Scoliidae" genus="Scolia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="miniata">
<emphasis box="[834,949,370,396]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">S. miniata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authority="Klug, 1832" authorityName="Klug" authorityYear="1832" box="[1170,1432,369,396]" class="Insecta" family="Scoliidae" genus="Scolia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lateralis">
<emphasis box="[1170,1293,369,396]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">S. lateralis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Klug, F." box="[1302,1432,369,395]" pageId="3" pageNumber="179" pagination="21 - 30" refId="ref3835" refString="Klug, F. (1832) Symbolae physicae seu icones et descriptiones insectorum quae ex itinere per Africam borealem et Asiam occidentalem Friderici Guilelmi Hemprich et Christiani Godofredi Ehrenberg studio novae aut illustratae redierunt. Vol. III. Insecta. Decas tertia. C. Mittler, Berolini [= Berlin], [183] pp., pls. 21 - 30." type="journal article" year="1832">Klug, 1832</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which is Egyptian. We refrain from formally synonymizing 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perez" authorityYear="1907" box="[871,1009,406,432]" class="Insecta" family="Scoliidae" genus="Discolia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="senescens">
<emphasis box="[871,1009,406,432]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">S. senescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Saussure" authorityYear="1859" box="[1074,1188,406,432]" class="Insecta" family="Scoliidae" genus="Scolia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="miniata">
<emphasis box="[1074,1188,406,432]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">S. miniata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but, consider that the most likely solution.
</paragraph>
